<div id="left">
	<img src=assets/WEATHER_SYSTEM_BURKE_WESTERN.Jpg>
	</div>

<div id="left">
	<p> 1.Starts in warm water near the equator 
<BR>
2.Warm water evaporates 
<BR>
3.Winds blow across Atlantic Ocean from Africa 
<BR>
4.Wind causes more warm water to evaporate 
<BR>
5.Water evaporates into the atmosphere where it cools 
<BR>
6.The evaporated water then condenses back into liquid water 
<BR>
7.Water droplets in the atmosphere become clouds 
<BR>
8.As the warm air rises upwards, it causes the air to spiral and increase in speed 
<BR>
9.As clouds and wind unify in their spiral, the speed increases 
<BR>
10.Once the winds reach 75 mph, it is considered to be an active hurricane 
<BR>
11.Once a hurricane hits land, the lack of warm air and water from the ocean body causes it to die down and eventually disapate 
<BR>
	</p></div>
